                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/7–844: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stewart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-07-08">July 8,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>296. The Nicaraguan Embassy here, under direct instructions from President
                    Somoza, has expressed the President’s indignation that an opposition political
                    group on July 4 should have used the American flag in a parade and meeting.</p>
                <p>Please report by telegram regarding this incident.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
